Rushcliffe Chief Executive to stand down

Rushcliffe Borough Council’s Chief Executive Allen Graham is to stand down at the authority after nearly 13 years in the role.

Council welcomes Forest proposals

Rushcliffe Borough Council has welcomed Nottingham Forest Football Club’s ambitions and plans to develop part of its City Ground stadium.

Get your business Brexit ready

Businesses preparing for the UK’s departure from the European Union (EU) can find out more about the latest implications and opportunities for their companies at a free Brexit Readiness event.

Be a Town or Parish Councillor

You can now find out more about standing as a Parish or Town Councillor in May by requesting a nominations pack from our elections team.
